  <p>

    The brown bear is a large bear species found across Eurasia and North America. 

    In North America, the populations of brown bears are called grizzly bears.

  </p>



  <h3>Characteristics</h3>

  <ul>

    <li>Large fur</li>

    <li>Powerful claws</li>

    <li>Omnivorous diet</li>

  </ul>



  <h3>Types of Bears</h3>

  <ol>

    <li>Brown Bear</li>

    <li>Polar Bear</li>

    <li>Black Bear</li>

  </ol>



